"title": "7435: sacrifice, in OT",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7435: sacrifice, in ot",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>An act that involved offering to God the life of an animal. It expressed gratitude for God's goodness or acknowledgment of sin. It was also associated with establishing a covenant.</p>\n<h2>Sacrifice was an integral part of worship</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:1\">GEN 46:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod10:24-Exod10:26\">EXO 10:24–10:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:19\">JDG 13:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:3\">1SA 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:4\">1KI 3:4</a></p>\n<h2>Sacrifices were a means of offering thanks to God</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:4\">GEN 4:4</a> <em>Abel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:20\">GEN 8:20</a> <em>Noah delivered from the flood</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:12\">EXO 18:12</a> <em>Jethro after God had delivered the Israelites</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:31\">JDG 11:31</a> <em>Jephthah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:15\">1SA 6:15</a> <em>after the safe return of the ark</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:3\">EZR 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra8:35\">EZR 8:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:6\">PSA 27:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps54:6\">PSA 54:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:17-Ps107:22\">PSA 107:17–107:22</a></p>\n<h2>Sacrifices were offered at regular religious festivals</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:5-Lev23:8\">LEV 23:5–23:8</a> <em>Passover</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:18-Lev23:20\">LEV 23:18–23:20</a> <em>the Feast of Weeks</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:23-Lev23:25\">LEV 23:23–23:25</a> <em>the Feast of Trumpets</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:6-Lev16:10\">LEV 16:6–16:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:26-Lev23:32\">LEV 23:26–23:32</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:33-Lev23:36\">LEV 23:33–23:36</a> <em>the Feast of Tabernacles</em></p>\n<h2>Special occasions were marked by sacrifices</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:63\">1KI 8:63</a> <em>the dedication of Solomon's temple</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:31-2Chr29:33\">2CH 29:31–29:33</a> <em>after Hezekiah had purified the temple</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:2-Ezra3:3\">EZR 3:2–3:3</a> <em>the Jews who returned from the Babylonian exile</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:17\">EZR 6:17</a> <em>at the completion of the second temple</em></p>\n<h2>Sacrifices as signs of individual and national penitence</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:1-Lev4:3\">LEV 4:1–4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:13-Lev4:14\">LEV 4:13–4:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:1-Judg2:5\">JDG 2:1–2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:26\">JDG 20:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:8-1Sam7:9\">1SA 7:8–7:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:10-2Sam24:25\">2SA 24:10–24:25</a></p>\n<h2>The place of sacrifice</h2>\n<h3>It was divinely chosen</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:13-Deut12:14\">DEU 12:13–12:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:3-Lev17:5\">LEV 17:3–17:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:2-Deut12:6\">DEU 12:2–12:6</a></p>\n<h3>Rival places of sacrifice caused the Israelites to sin</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:28-1Kgs12:29\">1KI 12:28–12:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:32\">1KI 12:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr15:17\">2CH 15:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:1\">2CH 31:1</a> <em>Under Hezekiah the high places were destroyed.</em></p>\n<h2>God condemned certain sacrifices</h2>\n<h3>Sacrifices to other gods</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:7-1Kgs11:8\">1KI 11:7–11:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num25:1-Num25:3\">NUM 25:1–25:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:4\">2KI 16:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:15\">2KI 16:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:28\">PSA 106:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:7\">ISA 57:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:3\">ISA 65:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:7\">ISA 65:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer19:4\">JER 19:4</a></p>\n<h3>Human sacrifices</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:21\">LEV 18:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:31\">DEU 12:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:34\">1KI 16:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:26-2Kgs3:27\">2KI 3:26–3:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:3\">2KI 16:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:31\">2KI 17:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:6\">2KI 21:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:31\">EZK 20:31</a></p>\n<h2>Sacrifice to the LORD may be rejected</h2>\n<h3>If it is a substitute for obedience</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:20-1Sam15:22\">1SA 15:20–15:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:21-Jer7:22\">JER 7:21–7:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos8:11-Hos8:13\">HOS 8:11–8:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:4\">AMO 4:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:33\">MRK 12:33</a></p>\n<h3>If it is a substitute for justice and mercy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:2-Isa66:3\">ISA 66:2–66:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:7-Mic6:8\">MIC 6:7–6:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:13\">MAT 9:13</a></p>\n<h3>If it is imperfect</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:13-Mal1:14\">MAL 1:13–1:14</a></p>\n<h2>Blessing is promised when right sacrifices are offered</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:15-Gen22:18\">GEN 22:15–22:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps4:5\">PSA 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:14-Ps50:15\">PSA 50:14–50:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:23\">PSA 50:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:17\">PSA 51:17</a></p>",
